RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 54. Claiming Purse 12500. (PLUS UP TO $2,500 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUEEN OF BEERS stalked the pacesetter from the onset, loomed up at the quarter pole and drew clear through the lane under steady urging. SI QUERE settled near the rear of the field, saved ground through the far turn while put to an early drive, and rallied belatedly to gain the place. BLONDES HAVEMO FUN broke alertly to take command from the gate, set a well measured pace and responded when called upon into the lane and weakened late in the drive. EUROROSE chased the leaders from the rail and failed to mount a rally in the stretch while traveling evenly. CHAPARRITA exchanged bumps with HIT'EM UP leaving the gate, dropped to the rear of the field and showed mild interest while rallying late behind horses. HIT'EM UP bumped at the start, raced up on the first turn to track the leaders from three wide, made a bid into the far turn and flattened out down the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 51. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. (PLUS UP TO $750 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GUITAR GROUPIE was well rated along the inside while racing down the backstretch, was gaining on the turn, shifted to the three path in the upper stretch, then kicked clear under a confident drive to prove best in the end. GOLD MEMORIES vied for the lead between rivals down the first half of the course, then dueled on the turn, continued to rally in the stretch then gave way in the late stretch and was best for second. SHACK IT TO ME was in a long drive to vie for the lead from the inside, then dueled with an outer rival on the turn, then gave way in the stretch. JULIE'S PASSION was allowed to settle along the inside down the backstretch and into the turn, then rallied in the upper stretch but it was too little to late. BLACK CHEETAH was unhurried early then settled on the backstretch while two wide, then bid in the home stretch and was no threat. MADAME RUE vied for the lead while three wide, was in a hard drive throughout the first half, was used up on the turn then dropped back.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DELIRIUM taken in hand from the gate, rated well off the leaders through the turn, swung five wide for the drive and prevailed to be going away at the wire. HARRY raced up the rail to duel for the early lead and was through after a half mile. SELLING SHORT broke alertly, dropped back steadily.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 4 7 1/2F Turf CR: 67. Allowance Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $1,675 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-wi nners Of A Race Since January 21, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since October 21, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile. If the race is for two year olds, it will be run at Seven Furlongs.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COLD NIGHT AIR lead the way into the first turn, then dueled down the backstretch, maintained stride throughout the turn, was confronted by a new rival heading into the stretch then edged clear in late stretch to prove best. RUN WITT RUN chased the pace while three wide, was urging on the far turn to challenge an inner rival for the lead in the early stretch, then was out finished on the end and held on for the place prize. TEXAS TWINKIES settled along the inside, bid on the turn to rally in the upper stretch then closed willingly in the end just missing the place position. KAUSE I'M DEVINE was rank early, then was unhurried, was moving up swiftly while three wide on the backstretch, bid from the two path on the turn to close well in the end but it was not enough. LEXINGTON DIVA dueled from the two path down the backstretch and into the turn, settled back along the inside, then rallied mid stretch, drifted out to the sixth path before giving way in the end. TRANQUILITY raced in the middle of the field along the rail into the turn, menaced in the stretch and was no threat. REASON OVER RICHES settled in the two path, then bid on the turn but did no respond in the stretch.
